# Signal subscriptions and lifetime

When adding or refactoring **`Signal<...>::Subscribe`** usage on types that **own** the subscription for the object’s lifetime (behaviours, environments, systems that outlive the callback):

1. **Prefer** [`SubscriptionsHolderBase.h`](src/Engine/Core/SubscriptionsHolderBase.h) — inherit or compose **`SubscriptionsHolderBase`** and call **`Subscribe(signal, callable)`** so all connections are released when the holder is destroyed or when **`UnsubscribeAll()`** runs.
2. **Avoid** calling **`signal.Subscribe(...)`** without keeping the returned **`ScopedSubscription`** (or an equivalent clear ownership story). Dropping the handle unsubscribes immediately; forgetting to tie lifetime to the owning object causes dangling callbacks or leaks of intent.

Direct **`Subscribe`** is still appropriate when the **`ScopedSubscription`** is **explicitly stored** (e.g. a dedicated member) and that storage’s lifetime is obviously correct — but default toward **`SubscriptionsHolderBase`** for consistency and bulk cleanup.
